This album is exactly what is says on the cover - the greatest creations of Eddy Grant, a versatile and underrated artist who fused elements of reggae and pop as well as some of his own styles to create simple yet powerful tunes, often with a political message.  Here you will find his biggest hits, the growling 'Electric Avenue' (including the ringbag remix, hugely popular in the UK), Baby Come Back, the dancefloor classic 'Nobody's Got Time', the long and cheerful greeting song 'Hello Africa' and the funk based, overtly political 'Living on the Frontline'
